# Hubly product direction

**Guiding principle:** Hubly should make owning a business feel as simple as describing one.

We are not building features. We are building **customer milestones**.

We are building the OS that helps local businesses **make more money with less effort**.

## North Star Metric

**Revenue generated through Hubly-powered businesses.**

If businesses earn money through Hubly: website, booking, payments, matching, and AI are working — and owners stay.

Do not optimize for websites created, CRMs, users, or merged PRs.

## Freeze

- Architecture, V1 scope, and launch checklist are frozen.
- No new Brain layers. No architecture PRs.
- Every sprint completes one milestone a real owner can depend on.

## Roadmap

[`docs/LAUNCH_CHECKLIST.md`](docs/LAUNCH_CHECKLIST.md) · [`docs/V1_RELEASE.md`](docs/V1_RELEASE.md)

**Current milestone: Business Launched** — a customer can successfully hire a business.

Hire journey (one experience, not disconnected features):

Website → services → package → available time → pay/deposit → confirmation → CRM → owner notify → calendar → shows in Hubly

## Sprint rule

Remove the largest blocker preventing a business from **earning money**.

Before merge: *Could a real business owner make more money because of this change?*  
If no — keep building.

## Never

- Fake success when Stripe/email/calendar Connection is missing  
- Skip ahead past hire/revenue blockers  
- Marketplace language for customers  
- Shipping infrastructure without a checked customer outcome  
